title: For Sale:  SMITH & WESSON ~ PRE-MODEL 27 3.5-Inch Shipped to QUANTICO in 1950...XLNT w/ Box..
postcontent: Here's a desirable Smith & Wesson revolver! This is a very early "Pre-Model 27" .357 Magnum. Even more interesting, it is fitted with the short 3.5-Inch barrel that was shipped to Quantico, Virginia, home of the FBI Academy! Built on the big-N frame with five screws, this revolver is factory finished in the highly polished bright blue. The "Pre-Model 27" was introduced in 1950 with the advent of the "short action" and this is a very early example! The Standard Catalog of Smith & Wesson mentions one source stating that the first Pre-Model 27 was serial number S75514, shipped 11/13/1950. This revolver is serial number S75969...but it shipped February 10, 1950!This revolver is in excellent overall condition.
